measurement: bd8 lowbd decode pipeline — Phase-3 integration reconciliation +
  Gate-3 ratio. Establishes that 0 of 4 ported lowbd families are wired into the
  aom-decode tile driver, verifies whole-pipeline byte-identity (highbd path,
  240-vector conformance), and freshly measures the current Ir ratio (unchanged
  by lowbd, improved only by the already-landed entropy/BCE levers 1+2).
git commit (measured): d00b07ad (origin/main at capture — "perf(dsp): CDEF lowbd
  — direct-u8-store SIMD + measured finding (delegate CDEF)"). NO decode code
  changed this pass; the tree is byte-identical to d00b07ad.
git commit (landing): the commit this .meta lands in.
date: 2026-07-22 (UTC ~08:10-08:45Z)
host: dedicated aom-rs workstation.
oracle: upstream/ submodule libaom v3.14.1 @ 03087864, Release, SIMD on, linked
  in-process via aom-sys-ref shim_decode_av1_kf.

COMMANDS (exact):
  # whole-pipeline byte-identity (job #2)
  AOM_CONFORMANCE_DIR=/root/aom-rs/conformance/data \
    cargo test -p zenav1-aom-decode --release conformance
  AOM_CONFORMANCE_DIR=/root/aom-rs/conformance/data AOM_FORCE_SCALAR=1 \
    cargo test -p zenav1-aom-decode --release \
    conformance_single_frame_intra_byte_identical_to_c_and_golden -- --nocapture
  # transform lowbd leaf-kernel differential (foundation still green)
  cargo test -p zenav1-aom-dsp --release --test inv_txfm2d_lowbd_diff
  # Gate-3 Ir (job #3)
  cargo build --profile profiling -p zenav1-aom-bench --bin gate3_profile
  AOM_CONFORMANCE_DIR=/root/aom-rs/conformance/data valgrind --tool=callgrind \
    --callgrind-out-file=/tmp/g3cg/cg_<cell>.out \
    ./target/profiling/gate3_profile dec port <cell> <iters>
    iters: dec_352x288_q00 = 3 (4 port decodes); dec_352x288_q32 = 12 (13).
  callgrind_annotate --inclusive=yes  → decode_frame_obus (port) / shim_decode_av1_kf (C).

RATIO METHOD: port = inclusive Ir of aom_decode::frame::decode_frame_obus divided
  by port-decode-count (iters+1, because assert_byte_exact does 1 extra port
  decode); C = inclusive Ir of shim_decode_av1_kf (1 decode). Ir deterministic,
  load-independent. The C shim includes codec init+destroy, which inflates C and
  therefore slightly UNDERSTATES port/C (most on the tiny q00 cell).

HONEST LIMITS:
- Gate 3 (<= 1.20x) NOT met. The lowbd pipeline closed 0% of the decode gap: 0/4
  families are wired; the port runs the wide u16 pipeline for bd8. The Ir-ratio
  improvement vs 2026-07-19 is the entropy/BCE levers 1+2, not lowbd.
- No fresh 4K wall-clock: the decode path is byte-identical to the code that
  produced the 2026-07-19 1.45x/1.39x wall-clock baseline (plus Ir-only levers
  that that meta states did not move the gate). Re-quoting 1.45x is not
  extrapolation; producing a NEW 4K number without running it would be.
- The two Ir cells are 352x288 (available conformance vectors). The 4K mosaic
  cells need generated vectors and a quiet box for wall-clock; not run this pass.
- Nothing extrapolated across sizes; every number reported was measured.
